## 4. Code Formatting (Spotless)

### 4.1 Auto-Format Before Commit

If Spotless check fails, auto-format your code:

```bash
mvn spotless:apply
```

Then stage and commit:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
```

---

### 4.2 Spotless Configuration

**Style:** Google Java Format with AOSP (4-space indentation)

**Configured in:** `pom.xml` (parent POM)

```xml
<plugin>
    <groupId>com.diffplug.spotless</groupId>
    <artifactId>spotless-maven-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>2.44.0</version>
    <configuration>
        <java>
            <googleJavaFormat>
                <version>1.23.0</version>
                <style>AOSP</style>
            </googleJavaFormat>
        </java>
    </configuration>
</plugin>
```

**Why AOSP style:**
- 4-space indentation (more readable than 2-space Google style)
- Industry-standard for Android and Spring Boot projects
- Consistent with existing Java ecosystem conventions

---

### 4.3 Known Issues

**Spotless Java 21 Compatibility:**
- **Issue:** Google Java Format has compatibility issue with Java 21
- **Error:** `NoSuchMethodError: 'java.util.Queue com.sun.tools.javac.util.Log$DeferredDiagnosticHandler.getDiagnostics()'`
- **Workaround:** Use `--no-verify` for non-code commits (Markdown, bash scripts)
- **Fix:** Upgrade Google Java Format to version compatible with Java 21 (TODO)

